-- Bakrie, Bukit Asam, United Tractors: Indonesian Equity Preview
-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 2012-04-23T01:46:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-23/bakrie-bukit-asam-united-tractors-indonesian-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have  unusual  moves in  Indonesian trading . Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index  rose 0.4 percent to 4,181.37.  PT Bakrie & Brothers (BNBR)  :  Indonesia ’s Bakrie family
received a default notice from creditors on a $437 million loan
after a drop in the shares of London-listed mining company Bumi
Plc that guaranteed the facility, the Financial Times reported.
Lenders led by Credit Suisse Group AG probably won’t demand
repayment even if the family fails to increase collateral, the
FT reported, citing people familiar with the deal. Bakrie &
Brothers, an  investment company , was unchanged at 50 rupiah.  PT Panorama Transportasi (WEHA)  : The tourism bus and
taxi operator said it plans to offer 100 billion rupiah ($11
million) of three-year bonds on May 10 and May 11 to repay bank
loans and purchase new vehicles. Panorama rose 3.1 percent to
165 rupiah.  PT Tambang Batubara Bukit Asam (PTBA)  : The company’s
first-quarter coal sales volume rose 26 percent to 3.9 million
tons from 3.1 million tons a year earlier, Kontan reported,
citing Hananto Budi Laksono, corporate secretary at an the
state-owned coal producer. Bukit Asam advanced 0.8 percent to
19,250 rupiah.  PT United Tractors (UNTR)  : Indonesia’s biggest heavy
equipment seller will allocate at least $500 million for capital
expenditure this year as it plans to invest in a mine-mouth
power plant project, Finance Director Gidion Hasan said. The
company sold 2,207 heavy equipment units in the first quarter of
this year, up from 2,200 units a year earlier, Hasan said.
United Tractors slid 0.3 percent to 31,150 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
